{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Position the mouse cursor over the snap target and run.\line Either run with a shortcut or bind to a mouse click action at 'Preferences -> Mouse modifiers' under Context: Media Item, Track or Ruler. Because the script responds to the mouse cursor position.\line To modify the script behavior in terms of item selection combine it within a custom action with such actions as:\line Item: Select item under mouse cursor; Item: Unselect all items\line and bind this custom action to a mouse click action.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In this script the edit cursor is not affected by the global Snap settings. You'd still want to have the regular behavior in another slot under Mouse modifiers.\par}
}

