{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In these '(un)collapse envelope lane' scripts 'track envelope' means envelope of TCP controls, those which are listed in the 'trim' (envelope) button context menu or under 'Track Envelopes' heading in the track envelope panel, including Send envelopes.\line 'FX envelope' means envelope of a track FX control.\line With toggle scripts uncollapsed state gets priority, so if at least one envelope lane in selected tracks is uncollapsed, it will be collapsed while collapsed lanes will stay as they are.\line Unidirectional scripts will always work according to their name, If there're no lanes to collapse or uncollapse nothing will happen.\line The scripts don't support creation of undo point due to REAPER internal design.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Moves selected FX envelope of a track to the top/bottom lane, upwards/downwards one lane depending on the script name.\line (cycle) in the script name means that all envelopes move upwards/downwards in unison with the selected one.\line (swap) in the script name means that the selected envelope is swapped with the one immediately above/below it while other envelopes maintain their lanes.\line Upwards/downwards movement is cyclic, i.e. if an envelope is pushed past top/bottom lane its movement continues from the oppostite end.\line Reordering only affects active envelopes of the track FX the selected envelope belongs to, as all envelopes of a particular FX are grouped together and envelopes of different FX cannot be mixed while TCP envelopes always precede any FX envelopes and themselves cannot be reordered. Hence the movement is not relative to ALL active/visible track envelopes but only to those of the same FX as the selected envelope.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Screenshot: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Buy-One/screenshots/main/Move%20selected%20FX%20envelope%20in%20track%20to%20top_bottom_upwards_downwards.gif\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 MK Shaper/Stutter is a script for quick envelope operations based on transients or rhythm grid.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 -The script is based on the time-tested MK Slicer. -Completely non-destructive audio processing based on envelopes manipulations. Realtime envelope operations. -Basic operations: Transient or Grid shaping (Ableton Sampler like), emphasizing or suppressing attacks, shortening the tails of sounds, gating percussion, steady rhythmic pulsation (stutter), sidechain pulsation based on transients or grid. Working with the grid also includes triplets and swing. -Ability to work with multitracks. Ability to work with many items. Ability to work with MIDI items (only in Grid mode). -The Attack parameter depends on the Velocity of the transients. Several modes are available.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Instructions for use:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Select one track and select the area with the item. Or: just select the item(s) on the same track without selecting an area. The script will not start, several tracks are selected.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Run the script.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Done! You can work. To form envelopes click "Shape". To cancel an actions, use "Reset" button. Reset sliders to default: Ctrl + Click. Fine tune: Shift + Drag(or MouseWheel). Exit the script: Esc, Space - Play. Also, after running the script, you can select the track on which you want to form an envelope and click "Shape".\sa180\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
