{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Snapshooter\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 https://github.com/tiagolr/reaper_scripts\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Snapshooter allows to create param snapshots and recall or write them to the playlist creating patch morphs. Different from SWS snapshots, only the params changed are written to the playlist as automation points.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Features:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Stores and retrieves FX params\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Stores and retrieves mixer states for track Volume, Pan, Mute and Sends\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Writes only changed params by diffing the current state and selected snapshot\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Transition snapshots using tween and ease functions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Writes transitions into time selection from current state to snapshot\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Tips:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Grab time selections and click write to write transitions into timeline\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Set global automation to READ to write snapshot from current state\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Use global automation BYPASS to write transitions when automation already exists on the playlist\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Snapshots can be written directly into cursor when there is no time selection\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If params are not writing make sure they have a different current value from the snapshot\sa180\par}
}

