{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 G U I D E\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The script displays FX preset menu of the object (track or item/active take) either currently found under the mouse cursor or the last selected if SEL_OBJ_IN_CURR_CONTEXT setting is enabled in the USER SETTINGS below, or of the currently or last focused FX chain window. With regard to track FX, for REAPER builds prior to 6.37 only TCP is supported.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab It's only able to list presets available in REAPER plugin wrapper drop-down list including imported .vstpreset files.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Since in multi-take items the menu only lists active take FX presets, if you need FX presets from a take other then the active simply click on it to have it activated.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Track preset menu is divided into two sections, main FX menu (upper) and input FX menu (lower) if both types of FX are present.\line In the Master track FX preset menu instead of the preset menu for input FX a menu for Monitor FX is displayed.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If there's active preset and plugin controls configuration matches the preset settings the preset name in the menu is checkmarked.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab The script can be called in the following ways:\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1)\tx360\tab by placing the mouse cursor over the object or its FX chain window and calling the script with a shortcut assigned to it;\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2)\tx360\tab by assigning it to a Track AND an Item mouse modifiers under {\i Preferences -> Mouse modifiers} and actually clicking the object to call it;\line If SEL_OBJ_IN_CURR_CONTEXT setting is enabled in the USER SETTINGS below:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3)\tx360\tab from an object right click context menu (main menus are not reliable);\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4)\tx360\tab from a toolbar, the toolbar must either float over the Arrange or be docked in the top or bottom dockers; Main toolbar or other docker positions are not reliable;\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5)\tx360\tab from the Action list (which is much less practicable)\line In cases 3)-5) the object must be selected as the mouse cursor is away from it.\line All five methods can work in parallel.\line Be aware that when SEL_OBJ_IN_CURR_CONTEXT setting is enabled and the script is run via a keyboard shortcut,the menu will be called even when the mouse cursor is outside of the TCP or Arrange and not over an FX chain window, like over the ruler, TCP bottom, empty Mixer area or any other focused window, in which case it will display a list of the last selected object FX presets.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab LOCK_FX_CHAIN_FOCUS setting in the USER SETTINGS allows displaying presets menu for FX of the last focused open FX chain even when the mouse cursor is outside of the FX chain window and it itself isn't in focus and regardless of the last selected object in case SEL_OBJ_IN_CURR_CONTEXT setting is enabled.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab To close the menu after it's been called, without selecting any preset, either click elsewhere in REAPER or pres Esc keyboard key.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Video processor preset menu is supported from REAPER build 6.26 onwards.\sa180\par}
}

