{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 tompad_FX_chain_AB\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Reascript for A/B-ing FX chains in Reaper DAW\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Use tompad_FX_chain_AB to compare different fx chains you create on a track.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 How to use:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Create a fx chain on a track.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Run tompad_FXchain_AB.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Make sure the track with the fx chain is selected and press Inject A-button.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Make a new fx chain on track OR make some adjustments to the fx chain and press Inject B-button.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Its now possible to compare the two fx chains by pressing the two big buttons A and B.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Requirements (from ReaPack):\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Reaper Tool Kit (rtk) from https://reapertoolkit.dev/index.xml\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Ultraschall API package from https://github.com/Ultraschall/ultraschall-lua-api-for-reaper/raw/master/ultraschall_api_index.xml\par}
}

