{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If there is a time selection covering part of both items, then it crossfades at the time selection area (items do not have to touch - closes the gap)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Can be used with as many items in different tracks as you like\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Smart undo point creation (only if there has been at least one change)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab You can set inside the script if you want to keep the time selection or remove it (default: remove)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab You can set inside the script if you want to keep selected the previously selected items or not (default: keep selected)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Default crossfade length and type are gotten automatically from Reaper Preferences ("Overlap and crossfade items when splitting, length" and "Default crossfade shape")\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Fade shape can be specified inside the script (overrides the one set in the Preferences)\sa180\par}
