{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This is a lua script based on MK SLICER 2 by @Cool for quick slicing, quantizing by grid, re-quantizing, triggering or sampling audio.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The original script has been modified to make it work with multitrack selection, especially useful for drum editing.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 No more "dummy" exports needed for multitrack editing, the script will sum the multi selection automatically, create peaks and find transients.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 No more selecting grouped items before slicing and quantizing, the script will do it for you with SLICEMODE options.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Faster editing with Grid related functions, the script only seeks transients related to the grid division you set.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 All awesome MK Slicer 2 features like single track midi triggering and sampling and randomize funtions are still in.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 80icio MODS\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Multitrack selection, editing, filtering\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Reduce Hit Points by Grid division\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Leading PAD\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Slicemode\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Added Mac Osx trackpad swipe gestures\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Improved GUI with better Trig lines and better Grid lines\par}
