\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Description\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Move and stretch selected events in the last clicked lane (notes, sysex, pitchwheel, CCs etc) to fit precisely into time selection.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Instructions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The script can be linked to a shortcut key or toolbar button, or it can be included in the CC lane context menu.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Description\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A simple script to insert a CC events, while leaving other events selected.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Strangely, current (v5.20) versions of REAPER do not offer any mouse modifiers for inserting CC events while keeping already-selected events selected.\line (Compare the "Insert note, leaving other notes selected" mouse action for notes.)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If snapping to grid is enabled in the MIDI editor, the event will be inserted at the closest grid position {\i before} the mouse position.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Useful for inserting a series of CC 'nodes' at precise grid positions, which can then be linked by linear ramps.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The script does not yet take swing into account when calculating grid positions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Instructions\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 There are two ways in which this script can be run:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1)\tx360\tab First, the script can be linked to its own shortcut key.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2)\tx360\tab Second, this script, together with other "js_" scripts that edit the "lane under mouse", can each be linked to a toolbar button.\line In this case, each script need not be linked to its own shortcut key. Instead, only the accompanying "js_Run the js_'lane under mouse' script that is selected in toolbar.lua" script needs to be linked to a keyboard shortcut (as well as a mousewheel shortcut). Clicking the toolbar button will 'arm' the linked script (and the button will light up), and this selected (armed) script can then be run by using the shortcut for the aforementioned "js_Run..." script. For further instructions - please refer to the "js_Run..." script.\sa180\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Description\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Inserts a pitch reset event at the start of each selected note.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If the mouse is over a main MIDI editor or inline MIDI editor, the editor under the mouse will be used.\line Otherwise (for example, if the mouse is over the action list), the last-focused main MIDI editor will be used.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 NOTE: Unlike most scripts, this script works on all editable takes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 WARNING: Getting all editable takes requires a tricky workaround. This script should therefore be regarded as a BETA release.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 DESCRIPTION\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 LFO generator and shaper - MIDI editor version\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Draw fancy LFO curves in REAPER's piano roll.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This version of the script applies the LFO to existing events -- velocities or CCs -- in the lane under the mouse.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 INSTRUCTIONS\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 DRAWING ENVELOPES\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Leftclick in open space in the envelope drawing area to add an envelope node.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Shift + Leftdrag to add multiple envelope nodes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Alt + Leftclick (or -drag) to delete nodes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Rightclick on an envelope node to open a dialog box in which a precise custom value can be entered.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Move mousewheel while mouse hovers above node for fine adjustment.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Use a Ctrl modifier to edit all nodes simultaneously:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Ctrl + Leftclick (or -drag) to set all nodes to the mouse Y position.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Ctrl + Rightclick to enter a precise custom value for all nodes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Ctrl + Mousewheel for fine adjustment of all nodes simultaneously.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The keyboard shortcuts "a", "c" and "r" can be used to switch the envelope view between Amplitude, Center and Rate.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 VALUE AND TIME DISPLAY\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The precise Rate, Amplitude or Center of the hot node, as well as the precise time position, can be displayed above the node.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Rightclick in open space in the envelope area to open a menu in which the Rate and time display formats can be selected.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 LOADING AND SAVING CURVES\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Click on the menu button at bottom left (or right-click anywhere outside envelope area) to open the Save/Load/Delete curve menu.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 One of the saved curves can be loaded automatically at startup. By default, this curve must be named "default".\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 FURTHER CUSTOMIZATION\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The menu also includes an option to skip redundant CCs while drawing the LFO.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Further customization is possible - see the instructions in the script's USER AREA.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This include:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Easily adding custom LFO shapes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Specifying the resolution of LFO shapes' phase steps.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Specifying the resolution of the mousewheel fine adjustment.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Changing interface colors.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Changing the default curve name.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab etc...\sa180\par}
}

