{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 DESCRIPTION\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Ajdusts audio items to tempo changes and playback rates, using stretch markers.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If the selected item already contains stretch markers, for example at transients, the existing markers will be adjusted to tempo changes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If the item does not yet contain any stretch markers, new markers will be added below each tempo change, and the slope of each stretch marker will follow linear tempo changes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Playback rates other than 1 will also be converted to stretch markers.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 DESCRIPTION\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A script for easy, one-click conversion of stretch markers in selected items to slopes with starting rate 1.0.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 By setting a starting rate of 1.0, time-stretching artefacts on the transient immediately after the marker are minimized.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 (Of course, as is the case for any time-stretch tactic, other artefacts may still arise.)\par}
}

