{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 DESCRIPTION\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script is a "beats version" of REAPER's native action "Time selection: Insert empty space at time selection (moving later items)". The number of selected beats is precisely replicated in the empty space.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 REAPER's action inserts empty space that is equal to {\i time} duration of the time selection. If the time selection is not an exact multiple of beats (calculated in the tempo preceding the insert point), all later events (including tempo changes) will necessarily shift away from their beat positions.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Tempo map\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script duplicates the tempo envelope into the empty space, which has the result of inserting the exact number of selected {\i beats} in the time selection. Later events will therefore remain on the grid.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Insert position\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The script can insert the empty beats/space on either the left of the right of the time selection, depending position of the edit cursor relative to the time selection.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Locked items\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The script will also detect locked items and can optionally protect such items against moving or splitting.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 MIDI items\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 MIDI items will {\i not} be split. Instead, the MIDI will be shifted {\i inside} the item. The script can therefore be used in the MIDI editor (NB: The current version of the script cannot yet insert beats into items that mix MIDI takes with audio takes and/or take envelopes.)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Timebase\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The user does not need to make any changes to the timebase before or after running the script. Items will be moved as if Timebase=Time for all tracks, items and envelopes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 WARNING\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The script may require several seconds to parse large MIDI items.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Provides a variety of options for creating time selections at the edit cursor, and can export specific settings as a separate action.\par}
}

