{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab REAPER: 6.02\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 DESCRIPTION:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This script randomized the order for the selected tracks. Useful for Blind-Tests\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 INTRODUCTION:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Select the tracks.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Run the Script\sa180\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Adds a track below the selected track with a click source for at least 220secs or more if the project is bigger.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The click track has ReaGate loaded and its volume will depend on the volume of the audio coming to its sidechain on channels 3&4. So, the metronome will play louder if the sidechain is louder and softer if it is softer ( in order to avoid bleed from the click track into the recording)\par}
}

