{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 Chord Gun\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 What is it?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Reaper tool that fires scale chords and notes into a composition, either by sequencing through the MIDI Editor or recording directly into Media Items\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 How do I use it?\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 There is an instructional video {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "www.youtube.com/watch?v=1CqVYcN3VAw"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
here
}}}
\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 keyboard shortcuts (when GUI has focus)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 0 - stop all notes from playing\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 1 - play scale chord 1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 2 - play scale chord 2\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 3 - play scale chord 3\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 4 - play scale chord 4\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 5 - play scale chord 5\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 6 - play scale chord 6\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 7 - play scale chord 7\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 q - higher scale note 1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 w - higher scale note 2\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 e - higher scale note 3\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 r - higher scale note 4\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 t - higher scale note 5\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 y - higher scale note 6\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 u - higher scale note 7\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 a - scale note 1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 s - scale note 2\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 d - scale note 3\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 f - scale note 4\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 g - scale note 5\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 h - scale note 6\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 j - scale note 7\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 z - lower scale note 1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 x - lower scale note 2\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 c - lower scale note 3\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 v - lower scale note 4\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 b - lower scale note 5\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 n - lower scale note 6\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 m - lower scale note 7\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ctrl+, - decrement scale tonic note\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ctrl+. - increment scale tonic note\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ctrl+shift+, - decrement scale type\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ctrl+shift+. - increment scale type\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 option+, - halve grid size\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 option+. - double grid size\par}
